         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
           <p>  
           <lb n="1"/>buddhasya bhagavataś śāsanānukā<space type="defect" quantity="1" unit="character"/>ritraipiṭakopāddhyaya
           <lb break="no" n="2"/>bhadantadharmmavatsa<space type="defect" quantity="1" unit="character"/>śiṣyasya śākyabhikṣor buddhaghoṣasya  
           <lb n="3"/>mahāgandha<space type="defect" quantity="1" unit="character"/>kuṭīvārikasya bhagavatpratimeyaṁ deyadharmmaṁ    
          </p> 
         </div>
          
          
          
          
         <div type="apparatus">
           
               <listApp>
                  <app loc="2">
                     <lem>śākyabhikṣor</lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Burgess+Buhler1883_01">bhikṣor</rdg>
                     <note>The reading is clear.</note>
                  </app>
                  <app loc="3">
                      <lem>deyadharmmaṁ</lem>
                      <rdg source="bib:Burgess+Buhler1883_01">deyadharmmaḥ</rdg>
                      <rdg source="bib:Gokhale1991_01">deyadharmmaḥ</rdg>
                      <note>There is only one dot on the eye-copy, estampage, and images.</note>
                  </app> 
               </listApp>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
          
         <div type="translation">
 	<p>This image of the Bhagavant is the pious gift of the <foreign>śākyabhikṣu</foreign> Buddhaghoṣa, the guardian of the great perfumed chamber and the pupil of the reverend Dharmmavatsa, [his] instructor, an expert in the Three <foreign>Piṭaka</foreign>s, who acts in accordance with the Teaching of the Bhagavant, the Buddha. </p>
         </div>
          
          
          
          
